nts1.d: Ross Allen knows music. Mainly new but plenty of old. The broadest range of music that moves dance floors from across the era’s and across the planet. On his regular Foundation Music Specials he invites guests to share their histories and seminal tracks…
From dub and dancehall to acid house and grime, London DJ, producer, and poet James Massiah showcases his references and creative influences

nts1.n: Horizons Créoles w/ Discos da Jajá
nts1.d: As Discos da Jajá, musician and record collector Helena Fontaine explores the poetics of Creole musical traditions, connecting the Caribbean, the Pacific, and Lusophone Africa via chouval bwa, gwo ka, kompa, morna, coladeira, maloya and semba, all drawn exclusively from vinyl archives.

An hour of timeless bossa nova, jazz and pop compositions from one of the original driving forces of Brazil's MPB movement, Rio's Edu Lobo.
Selected by Palo Santo Discos.
A swift hour long excursion into the unknown. Expect the unexpected from host Tom Cathcart as almost anything goes: techno, post-punk, minimal synth, dub and new wave. Don’t be a prude.
Sweet selections from director and photographer Alfie Whiteman.
Babak Ganjei's monthly grunge and garage hangover rolls through with classics old and new, from Memphis to London, interspersed, of course, with totally irrelevant jokes and chat.
Cherrie Flava, the boss of MIC Records, the London label behind releases from LAPS, Mike Collins, Lord Tusk & more, joins us once a month.

nts1.d: Two hours of Canadian-made cassette ambient, new age and downtempo sounds from the 1980s, selected by NTS.

nts2.d: The legend that is Andy Votel strolls into our Manchester studio once a month to play a portion of his record collection selected at random.
Daniel Jahn of Hamburg record shop Bureau B join us for semi-regular hour-long outings.

nts2.n: ACROSS THE HORIZON W/ BOB HOLMES (SUSS)
nts2.d:
Across the Horizon is a bold exploration of where Americana’s roots intersect with the boundless expanse of ambient music. Hosted by Bob Holmes, member of SUSS, and host of the popular Ambient Country podcast, this unique program invites you into a realm where sound becomes landscape, and music transcends genre, inviting listeners to wander through vast, uncharted spaces of sonic possibility.
From The Host: In this episode of the Across the Horizon Radio Hour, host Bob Holmes (of SUSS) is joined by guest curator Cynthia Bernard aka marine eyes for an entire hour dedicated to the music of women in ambient Americana, including artists like Yasmin Williams, Marisa Anderson, Mary Lattimore and many more.
In the mix with Simon Parris, blending and rearranging cross-genre music and sonic fragments. Chiaroscuro moments from then and now…
Annabel Fraser is a lover of music first and foremost. Not genres. Tune in for her monthly 2 hour show…

Centred around forward-thinking club music and experimental sounds, Mutualism functions as a label, mix series and club night with a focus on inclusivity, exploration and collaboration.
From the host: "I feel like the apocalypse is creeping under the door, UK rappers always know how to soundtrack the apocalypse, thus and therefore."
Todmorden's finest, Kim Lana joins us in the Manchester studio once a month for 2 hours of bumping and pumping golden era house & techno.

Bergsonist is a musician originally from Morocco based in NYC. Genre-free sonic explorations with occasional conversations/guest mixes featuring inspiring artists.
From the host: I wanted to thank Sam for his mix, you can find Sam Clarke's IG: https://www.instagram.com/3sam3clarke3/
and his label Rank + File bandcamp (featuring a beautiful release by Gaul Plus (tip+++)): https://rankandfile.bandcamp.com/music
Thank you for tuning in!
Tokyo-based DJ & composer Abiu taking you to a higher state, playing tracks from across the house axis.
‘Run it Red’ sees bona fide techno legend Ben Sims showcases 2 hrs of the finest new house and techno he can lay his hands on.
BFDM, a.k.a Brothers From Different Mothers, are the snottiest techno label around. Non-stop crunch rollers, all the way from Lyon - tune in for an hour on 2, monthly Mondays.

nts2.n: A MONTH OF SUNDAYS W/ BILL SPENCER (R)
MUSIC FOR A HEALING EARTH W/ THE COSMIC TONES RESEARCH TRIO (R)

subtle.d: Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Vinyl DJ from Leigh-on-Sea. Loves collecting records with a wide array of taste ranging from House and Techno to Grime, Dubstep and Jungle. Garage holds a special place in his heart and makes up the largest part of my collection and DJ sets.

DJ & Producer hailing from Watford influenced by Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Grime with releases on NSX records & Ghost Phone, spinning electronic genres from R&B edits, Drum and Bass and everything in between.
Highlander brings you 2 hours of the freshest Jungle, Hardcore, Dubstep and Breaks. 3rd Saturday 7-9pm lock in!

2Step Selects is a monthly show hosted by the Choki Biki Records crew. Founded in Dublin, Ireland, CBR consists of DJ Sharpson, 2step.png, Frame Shift, and MICK. The show consists of an all round breaks, electro, ukg and jungle hour, followed by an Irish showcase, demonstrating all the best Ireland has to offer collective/party/Dj & Producer wise!

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

subtle.n: The Ice Box Sessions with Frigid

subtle.d: Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

subtle.n: Out of Phase With Sam Ling

subtle.d: Sessions w/ Amy B is an underground multi-genre music show, showcasing the most prolific guests from all corners of the music industry.

Originally linking up in Wellington and playing shows with the Breaking Beats crew, Swampman and Zero Crumbs have reunited – bringing their smooth mixing and flexible selections to East London. 

In their monthly show, the pair explore the deep, dark, and soulful ends of DNB. Expect fresh underground tunes, deep cut classics, and a bit of banter in Kiwi accents.

subtle.d:

Has released on Keysound recordings, RKS, eatmybeat, ec2a, Durkle Disco and Dimsum records

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
Peak Oil records presents ‘tipping point’; a monthly journey through the record collections of brian and brion. Leaving no good genre unturned, enjoy two hours of esoterica, conversation and guests.
